Job Title: Human Resources (HR) Manager
Location: Islamabad, Pakistan
Company: Veritas Technologies Pvt. Ltd.
Department: Human Resources
Job Type: Full-Time
Reports To: Director of Operations

Position Overview
Veritas Technologies is looking for a strategic and people-oriented HR Manager to oversee our company’s human resources operations and ensure alignment with business objectives. The successful candidate will be responsible for developing HR strategies, managing employee relations, supporting talent acquisition and retention, and cultivating a high-performance culture across all departments.

Key Responsibilities
Develop and implement HR policies and procedures aligned with company goals

Manage the full employee lifecycle: recruitment, onboarding, performance management, and exit procedures

Lead organizational development efforts including employee engagement, training programs, and leadership development

Serve as a trusted advisor to management and staff on HR-related matters

Resolve employee grievances, mediate disputes, and ensure a positive working environment

Ensure legal compliance with local labor laws and regulations

Maintain and update HR systems, records, and documentation

Prepare HR reports and dashboards for management review

Collaborate with department heads to assess staffing needs and workforce planning

Drive DEI (Diversity, Equity & Inclusion) and wellness initiatives

Qualifications
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or a related field

5–8 years of progressive HR experience, with at least 2 years in a managerial role

Strong knowledge of labor laws and HR best practices in Pakistan

Excellent interpersonal, communication, and leadership skills

Proficiency with HRIS platforms (e.g., BambooHR, Zoho People) and MS Office Suite

High emotional intelligence and conflict-resolution abilities

Strategic thinking with a hands-on approach to problem-solving

Preferred Qualifications
HR certifications (e.g., SHRM-CP, PHR, CHRP)

Experience working in the tech, services, or startup ecosystem

Familiarity with change management and organizational restructuring

What We Offer
Competitive salary and annual performance bonuses

Medical insurance (including dependents)

Paid time off and wellness leave

Hybrid work policy

Learning & development budget

Supportive leadership and a collaborative culture

Application Process
Please send your CV and cover letter to hr@veritastech.pk with the subject line:
HR Manager – [Your Full Name]
Application Deadline: June 30, 2025
